This paper deals with natural language generation and evaluation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of language models and probabilistic modeling suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the mention of a novel WordPiece-based version and the use of a benchmark dataset suggest a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
